sentences: Hedwige (Gennaro)-Chrétien (15 July 1859 – 1944) was a French composer.
Born in Compiègne, Chrétien was appointed professor at the Paris Conservatoire in 1889 where she had previously been a student from 1874, studying with Ernest Guiraud.
